ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[_Trichomonas gallinae_ is a flagellated protozoan. It is not easy to
diagnose trichomonas. This disease may be confused with others that look
very similar, such as Vitamin A deficiency, candidiasis and poxvirus. In
order to distinguish the difference, oral fluids or a scraping taken from
the crop or from an oral lesion and tested by PCR can distinguish between
these diseases.
Although bird feeding is an enjoyable hobby, sanitation is essential for
the health of the birds that dine at these readily available avian
restaurants. - Mod.TG]
